1) Configuring ArgoCD with GKE

    Prerequisite:
        a. GKE cluster
        b. IAM permissions

    1.1 Installation of ArgoCD:
        kubectl create namespace argocd
        kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

    1.2 Download and Install ArgoCD CLI:
        curl -sSL -o argocd-linux-amd64 https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases/latest/download/argocd-linux-amd64
        sudo install -m 555 argocd-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/argocd
        rm argocd-linux-amd64

    1.3 Access the ArgoCD API server:
    By default the ArgoCD API server is exposed as a ClusterIP service type. We can access it by Port Forwarding without exposing the service.

        kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443 --address 0.0.0.0

        ( you can access argocd on <public-ip-address>:8080 )

    1.4 Get the admin password:
        kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o jsonpath=”{.data.password}”

        This will give the output in base64 encoded format. You have to decode it first.

