2) GKE Ingress Configuration

    2.1 Disable internal TLS (Transport Layer Security):
    To disable internal TLS, we need to pass the --insecure flag to the argocd-server command, this will avoid an internal redirection loop from HTTP to HTTPS. For this, we need to edit the deployment named “argocd-server” and make the following changes

    containers:
    - command:
      - argocd-server
      - --insecure  (changed)

    Now server will not redirect it to HTTPS

    or

    We can set server.insecure: “true” in the “argocd-cmd-params-cm” ConfigMap as shown below:

    data:
        server.insecure: "true"

    2.2 Create an externally accessible service:
        We need to create an externally accessible service which will be a ClusterIP service type and have annotation as (Network Endpoint Group) NEG that will allow your load balancer to send traffic directly to your pods without the kube-proxy being used.

        apiVersion: v1
        kind: Service
        metadata:
          name: argocd-server-svc
          namespace: argocd
          annotations:
            cloud.google.com/neg: '{"ingress": true}'
            cloud.google.com/backend-config: '{"ports": {"http":"argocd-backend-config"}}'
        spec:
          type: ClusterIP
          ports:
          - name: http
            port: 80
            protocol: TCP
            targetPort: 8080
          selector:
            app.kubernetes.io/name: argocd-server

    2.3 Create BackendConfig:

        Create Backend Config which is being referenced in external service to perform health checks.

        apiVersion: cloud.google.com/v1
        kind: BackendConfig
        metadata:
          name: argocd-backend-config
          namespace: argocd
        spec:
          healthCheck:
            checkIntervalSec: 30
            timeoutSec: 5
            healthyThreshold: 1
            unhealthyThreshold: 2
            type: HTTP
            requestPath: /healthz
            port: 8080

    2.4 Create FrontendConfig:

        Now we will create Frontend Config that will redirect HTTP to HTTPS.

        apiVersion: networking.gke.io/v1beta1
        kind: FrontendConfig
        metadata:
          name: argocd-frontend-config
          namespace: argocd
        spec:
          redirectToHttps:
            enabled: true


    2.5 Create Global Static IP:

        gcloud compute addresses create argocd-ingress-ip-address  --global --ip-version IPV4


    2.6 Create ManagedCertificate:

        Here we will be creating Managed SSL certificate which will be used in the Load balancer

        apiVersion: networking.gke.io/v1
        kind: ManagedCertificate
        metadata:
          name: argocd-cert
          namespace: argocd
        spec:
          domains:
            - argocd.xyz.com


    2.7 Create Ingress:

        Finally, we will be creating an Ingress object which is having reference to our frontend config, service, and managed certificate.

        apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
        kind: Ingress
        metadata:
          name: argocd-ingress
          namespace: argocd
          annotations:
            kubernetes.io/ingress.global-static-ip-name: argocd-ingress-ip-address
            networking.gke.io/managed-certificates: argocd-cert
            networking.gke.io/v1beta1.FrontendConfig: argocd-frontend-config
        spec:
          rules:
            - host: argocd.xyz.com
              http:
                paths:
                  - path: /
                    pathType: Prefix
                    backend:
                      service:
                        name: argocd-server-svc
                        port:
                          number: 80





